  "body":"*If you aren't sure about your bug, you can always join our [Discord](https://discord.gg/HNmxvpm) and ask in #agora or #engineering!*\r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n\r\n- A Reddit user reported that when the user changes block content and then change block indentation, there will be a short time when the block is empty.\r\n- If the changed block content contains links (for link detection) and the cursor is moved away from the block, modified content would not be visible for a short time.\r\n\r\n**Expected Behavior**\r\n\r\nContent display should be consistent without flickering.\r\n\r\n**Dependencies**\r\n\r\n[ Please specify your environment and software dependencies, with versions. ]\r\n\r\n- Athens: latest master, my dev build\r\n- browser: Chrome (macOS)\r\n- JVM: java8u251\r\n- node.js: v13.12.0\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n\r\nSee _problem_ section.\r\n",
